Even at _t_ mid=0 _._ 5, where approximately half the sequence is revealed, _∼_ 32 positions still vary across completions. These remaining variable positions are precisely the ones most susceptible to compounding errors at
subsequent midpoints: they are unrevealed tokens where the stochastic jump makes a consequential choice.
Navigation shaping targets exactly these positions—the sequence phase selects the globally best candidate
across all variable positions, and the token phase corrects individual misalignments within the winner.

