509994,0.07291200108738849,0.0,49370.39191800068,graph,18,0.0,"{'response': 'Combining simulators can help by reducing the gap between real and simulated user behaviors. According to paper 2605.07847v1, when randomly sampling which Large Language Model (LLM) serves as the user simulator for generating conversations, significant reductions in Jensen–Shannon divergence scores are observed across coding and writing tasks. This indicates that combining certain simulators can improve the realism of interactions.', 'retrieved': [{'candidate_answer': 'Combining simulators helps by demonstrating that the rankings produced by different clustering algorithms are nearly identical, indicating robustness. The Spearman rank correlations between simulator rankings across all pairs of clustering methods (k-means, Gaussian Mixture Models, and Agglomerative Clustering) are very high (ρ ≈ 0.96), suggesting consistency in behavior distribution despite the use of different algorithms.', 'score': 100}, {'candidate_answer': 'Combining simulators that are behaviorally complementary can help reduce the distributional gap between simulated and real user behaviors. This approach is similar to mixture-of-experts strategies and could be extended by learning a router to select the appropriate simulator.', 'score': 95}, {'candidate_answer': 'Combining simulators can help by allowing the validation of user behavior representation embeddings. By constructing datasets from both real and simulated embeddings, linear classifiers are trained to distinguish between them. The high classification accuracies across different simulators indicate that these embeddings effectively capture meaningful differences in user behavior. This process helps in understanding how similar or distinct the behaviors generated by various simulators are compared to each other and to real users.', 'score': 95}, {'candidate_answer': 'Combining simulators, as discussed in paper [28], can help by leveraging multiple user simulators to train task-oriented dialogue systems. This approach allows for a more diverse and realistic interaction experience, which is crucial for improving the performance of such systems.', 'score': 95}, {'candidate_answer': 'Combining simulators can help reduce the gap between real and simulated user behaviors according to paper 2605.07847v1. By randomly sampling which LLM serves as the user simulator for generating conversations, the study reports that forward KL divergence (KL), backward KL divergence (KL bwd), and Jensen–Shannon divergence (JS) across coding and writing tasks show improvements when combining certain simulators. For instance, the combination of `gemma-4-31B-it` and `Claude Haiku 4.5` shows significant reductions in JS scores for both coding and writing tasks.', 'score': 90}], 'verbose': {'selected_set': [{'v': '2605.07847v1_chunk_18', 't': 'DocumentChunk'}, {'v': '2605.07847v1_chunk_25', 't': 'DocumentChunk'}, {'v': '2605.07847v1_chunk_24', 't': 'DocumentChunk'}, {'v': '2605.07847v1_chunk_17', 't': 'DocumentChunk'}, {'v': '2605.07847v1_chunk_27', 't': 'DocumentChunk'}, {'v': '2605.07847v1_chunk_28', 't': 'DocumentChunk'}, {'v': '2605.07847v1_chunk_29', 't': 'DocumentChunk'}, {'v': '2605.07847v1_chunk_35', 't': 'DocumentChunk'}, {'v': '2605.07847v1_chunk_15', 't': 'DocumentChunk'}, {'v': '2605.07847v1_chunk_33', 't': 'DocumentChunk'}, {'v': '2605.07847v1_chunk_34', 't': 'DocumentChunk'}, {'v': '2605.07847v1_chunk_16', 't': 'DocumentChunk'}, {'v': '2605.07847v1_chunk_23', 't': 'DocumentChunk'}], 'start_set': [{'v': '2605.07847v1_chunk_35', 't': 'DocumentChunk'}, {'v': '2605.07847v1_chunk_17', 't': 'DocumentChunk'}, {'v': '2605.07847v1_chunk_25', 't': 'DocumentChunk'}, {'v': '2605.07847v1_chunk_18', 't': 'DocumentChunk'}, {'v': '2605.07847v1_chunk_29', 't': 'DocumentChunk'}], 'final_retrieval': {'2605.07847v1_chunk_24': [""10\n\n\n[18] Grosz, B. J. and Sidner, C. L. (1986). Attention, intentions, and the structure of discourse.\ninl lC **ota** mpu **i