According to paper 2605.07847v1, measuring the distributional gap is important because it helps in understanding how closely simulated user behaviors align with real users' behaviors. This is crucial for improving conversational AI systems by reducing discrepancies and enhancing their performance. The paper specifically mentions that combining pairs of simulators can reduce the gap to real users, as evidenced by the reported divergence metrics (KL divergence, backward KL divergence, and Jensen–Shannon divergence) in Table 3.

